ingredients.Name: Yukon gold potatoes, chopped into 1 inch ish cubes

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 425F. Add potatoes to baking sheet, drizzle with some olive oil, Italian seasoning blend, salt and pepper and toss to coat. Bake at 425F for 30-45 minutes or until tender, golden, and crispy. The timing will all depend on how big you cut your potatoes.

Heat a large skillet over medium high heat and add about 1 tbsp oil. Add the breakfast sausage in clumps and leave undisturbed to cook and crisp for about 3-5 minutes. Then use your spatula to break it up and continue cooking until no pink remains. Use a slotted spoon to remove and set aside.
Add the peppers and onions to the pan and cook, stirring often, until softened and maybe even frizzling around the edges. Remove from the heat and set aside.

Assemble the jars! Add in the potatoes, peppers and onions, sausage, and spinach evenly among the 8 jars (or however many you choose to make). Loosely put on the lid initially for freezing and then once frozen you can tighten it all the way. This will help prevent the glass from baking if there is any expansion.
My plan to reheat is to just dump the contents into a pan, cook, then add some eggs to round it out.
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Postpartum Breakfast Freezer Cups
Description:
Breakfast really is the most important meal of the day, in my humble option, and I’m not planning on skimping on it while postpartum. 
I knew that I wanted to prep some freezer cups that were packed with nutrients, carbs, and protein to fill me up and sustain me through the sleepless nights. 

Yes, I’ll be adding eggs during the reheat process… but that seems easy enough. Right? 👀

ingredients.Name: heads broccoli chopped, about 2 to 3 cups worth
shredded cheddar cheese (I used Raw Farm USA)

directions.Direction: Add butter to a dutch oven or large pot and melt over medium heat.
Add in the diced onions and cook until softened/translucent.
Add in the all purpose flour and whisk to incorporate. Let that cook for about 2 minutes to toast a bit.
Pour in the buttermilk and whisk again to combine with the toasted all purpose flour mix.
Add the carrots, broccoli, bone broth, and garlic and let simmer for about 15-25 minutes. You want the carrots to soften!
Pour in the heavy cream, mixie mix, and slowly add in the cheese stirring as you add.
You can leave the soup as is, but I like to blend it up a bit with an immersion blender!
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Buttermilk Broccoli Cheddar Soup
Description:
Yes, there's still cream in it, but the addition of buttermilk makes this Broccoli Cheddar Soup just a lil different. 

It's incredibly easy to make and makes great leftovers!

ingredients.Name: pie crust from THE Flaky Pie Crust

directions.Direction: Begin with one blind baked pie shell. (directions in THE Flaky Pie Crust)
Preheat oven to 350F
Add cheese, broccoli, and chopped scallions. Add some salt and pepper just to season.
Mix eggs, cream, and milk until fully incorporate.
Add egg mixture to the quiche and cover the additions. The broccoli may be sticking out a little bit, but that's ok!
Bake at 350F for 45-60 minutes - until the center is slightly giggly but set.
Let cool for SEVERAL hours to fully set! I usually let mine set overnight.
You can totally eat this cold, but I love it warmed up in the toaster oven.
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Broccoli Cheddar Quiche
Description:
There are few things I love more than quiche. It's feels so decadent and yet is so easy to make. 
I use my Flaky Butter Pie Crust recipe, but you can always buy store bought crust. Though, trust me, my recipe is so good.
Broccoli, cheddar, and scallion is the absolute perfect combo here. You're gonna love it.

ingredients.Name: Oil for cooking (ideally olive, algae, tallow, or ghee)
large yellow or white onion, diced
red, yellow, or orange bell pepper, diced
collards, stems removed, leaves roughly chopped
whole milk ricotta, plus more for topping

directions.Direction: Heat oil in a large dutch oven or pot over medium high heat. Once shimmering add in 1 pound of ground beef at a time. Add the beef to the pan in chunks, trying to maintain some bit of space between each piece while still getting as much surface area as possible. Let that cook undisturbed for 5-7 minutes, until the bottom is deeply browned. This will bring SO MUCH flavor! During this time season it with salt and pepper. Use a spatula or spoon to stir and break up the beef. Cook for 1-2 more minutes and transfer to a bowl. Repeat with the other pound of beef and set aside.

Lower the heat to medium. Now that you have a bunch of beef fat in the pan, add in the garlic, onion, and pepper. Let that cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and onions are turning translucent. If you see the onions browning, move on!
Add in the collards and tomatoes and cook until wilted, just 1-2 minutes.
Add the bone broth, increase the temp to medium/high, and bring to a boil. Once boiling add the gnocchi and cook until the gnocchi starts to float to the top.

Turn the heat to medium/low and add in the marinara (pro tip: add a tiny bit of water to the jar after everything has been poured out, shake it up, and use that remaining watery marinara), and 1/2 cup of ricotta. Stir to combine and taste for seasoning. You’ll likely have to add a decent amount of salt.
Serve with an additional dollop of ricotta.
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Protein Packed Gnocchi Lasagna Soup
Description:
This gnocchi soup is probably more of a beef soup plus gnocchi than a gnocchi soup plus beef. But that just doesn’t sound as enticing. 😉

I wanted this to have all the vibes of lasagna without actually being lasagna. Now that I’m pregnant my first and foremost concern is getting in a ton of protein with every meal! 🤰🏼

You can always double up on the gnocchi if you want a little pillowy bit in every bite, but I personally wanted the gnocchi to be present without giving me carb overload. 🤌🏻

Between the marinara (I used Summer Lemon Marinara from @getsauz 🍋🍅) and ricotta I promise it’ll feel like you’re eating lasagna but in the healthiest and bestest way. 🥰

Plusss let’s chat nutrients:
✨Bell peppers contain 3x the amount of Vitamin C as an orange
✨Swiss chard packs on iron, magnesium, potassium, and vitamins A, C, and K
✨Collagen provides essential amino acids 
✨Beef (always @butcher_box) provides protein, iron, zinc, selenium, vitamin B6, vitamin B12, magnesium, and potassium.

ingredients.Name: lemon zest (feel free to add more)
melted butter (divided: 4 tbsp for the muffins and 4 tbsp for the topping)
honey (if you don't want multiple sweeteners just use maple syrup)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 425F and prep 12 muffin tins. I like to use cast iron muffin tins and brush melted butter on the insides. Use whatever you have an feel free to use muffin liners or parchment if you prefer.
Combine all dry ingredients: flour, polenta, salt, and baking soda in a large bowl.
In a medium bowl whisk to combine maple syrup, sourdough discard, milk, egg, lemon zest, vanilla extract, and 4 tablespoons melted butter.
Pour the wet ingredients into the dry and use a wooden spoon to incorporate. Stop immediately once combined and no dry streaks remain. Add in the blueberries and mix just to combine.
Divide evenly among your prepped muffin tins, doing your best to only fill 3/4 of the way up.
Combine oats, honey (or maple syrup), remaining 4 tbsp butter, and a dash of salt.

Top each muffin with just under 1 tbsp of oat mixture. If you leave it all in a clump it'll sort of sink down when the muffin cooks and create a deliciously sweet oat core in the center. You can also try to spread it out a little more to achieve more of a topping.
Bake at 425F for 14-17 minutes. Use a toothpick or cake tester to poke for doneness - if it comes out dry you're good to go. *refer to notes for more tips*
Let cool for 5-10 minutes in the tins and then remove and cool completely on a wire rack. Or just get them on the rack and start eating immediately.
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Guilt Free Sourdough Blueberry and Oat Core Muffins
Description:
This recipe was born from the need to make use of Sourdough Discard. Anyone that has an active starter knows the feeling all too well. 
Though, this might be my favorite use for the discard to date!

They're refined sugar free and pack on a ton of nutrients. 

The muffins have crisp edges thanks to polenta and butter, the inside is tender from the tart blueberries, and the oat topping that sort of turns into an oat coreeee. It's sweet without being sickeningly, it's tender without being mushy, it's everything I want in a muffin. 

Since they're refined sugar free and pack on tons of nutrients from the blueberries and oats, these are the perfect guilt free breakfast muffin.
Notes:
*To test for doneness: If you stick the tester into the oat topping area it will appear to not be done. Make sure you're poking in a topping free zone. 
*To test for doneness: The polenta can sorta of make a thicker crust on the outside of the muffin, so it may keep any wet bits from coming through when you pull it out... since this is a possibility I recommend just looking at the outside of the muffins. You're looking for crisp and browning around the edges! 
*To keep the blueberries from bleeding color into the batter you can first toss them in the dry mixture or some flour before adding. However, I think the blue tones are beautiful and look like a galaxy cake meets muffin.

ingredients.Name: yellow onion, chopped into 1 in chunks
balsamic vinegar (can sub with whatever vinegar you have)
celery, cut on a steep bias
carrots, cut into 1 inch chunks on a bias
large sweet potato, cut into 1.5 in cubes

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 325F
Set a large dutch oven over medium high heat. Add in olive oil and heat until shimmering, but not smoking!

Cook the beef in 2 batches to ensure everything gets nice and browned. Season well with salt and pepper! Cook beef on 2 sides and allow each side to sit undisturbed for 3-5 minutes, or until a nice brown crust has formed. Once everything is cooked remove and set aside (I like to just add it to the inside of lid to the dutch oven so I don't dirty another plate or bowl)

Add the onion, garlic, and ginger to all dat fat and cook for about 1-3 minutes. You don't want to burn the garlic here. Once sizzling and the onion has taken on the slightest bit of color add in the anchovies and fry until dissolved, stirring frequently.
Add the meat back in, the pumpkin, and balsamic. Stir to combine everything.
Add in the flour, stir to fully incorporate. Then add in the water and bone broth. Stir to combine.
Pop the lid on and bake in the preheated oven at 325F for 1 1/2-2 hours. 1 1/2 will do the trick but 2 hours is better if you have the time.

Remove from the oven and add in the coconut milk and veggies. Mixie mix to combine then pop dat back in the oven, lid on, for another hour. Remove the lid and cook for another 20-30 minutes. We just want to give the meat a litttttle extra time to soften and the broth to thicken.
Taste and season with extra salt to your liking. Daniel topped his with some hot sauce, so go for it if you like it spicyyyy!
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Pumpkiny n’ Coconuty Sweet Potato BEEF STEW
Description:
I’m not sure I’ll ever love a stew recipe more. 👏🏻

Traditionally beef stew has some red wine in it. NOT THIS ONE. Not your girl. 
If you don’t already know this, I don’t drink alcohol. So that means I don’t BUY alcohol. So it’s not like if I want a beef stew I’m gonna whip out a bottle of red wine. And I’m sure you’re thinking “just buy some wine you idiot”. But guess what? I don’t want to. I rather make a broth FILLED with things that are actually GREAT for me. 

The broth has the nutrient power house, pureed PUMPKIN, plus coconut milk and bone broth for hydration. It’s thick, creamy, and ULTRA flavorful.

I mean the stew also has sweet pototez and a ton of other immune boosting produce, but idk the broth here really makes me happy.

And while this does take several hours to make it’s not like a whole day thing… unless you want to throw it in a crock pot then you do you. 

The meat is pull apart tender. The veg are perrrrfectly softened but not smooshie.  

It’s a warm hug in my tummy and I wish we hadn’t blown through the leftovers so fast and I could eat more now.

ingredients.Name: medium winter squash cut in half and seeds removed (any variety will do but a butternut, honey nut, or kabocha work great!) You want about 2 cups of flesh after roasting
carrots, cleaned and tops trimmed off
knob of ginger, peeled and chopped
coconut milk, plus more for topping
Olive oil for roasting and cooking!

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 425F.

Place squash (cut side up) and carrots on a rimmed baking sheet. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Turn over the squash (so it's now cut side down) and shake everything around to get the oil and seasoning all over. Bake at 425F for 30 minutes.

While that's baking, dump all of the seeds and flesh into a bowl of water. Use your fingers to break the seeds off of the flesh. They'll float to the top so you can just strain them out! Place on a towel to try off, then add to another baking sheet. Drizzle with more olive oil and sprinkle with salt, pep, garlic powder, onion powder, and smoked paprika. Pop those in when the squash has 7-10 minutes left!
Heat ghee or oil in a large pot set over medium heat. Add in the onion, ginger, garlic, and habanero. Cook for 5-7 minutes or until softened and onion is starting to take on some brown color.
Add in the tahini, mixie mix, and then immediately pour in the broth. Make sure to scrape the bottom of the pot to release any browned bits.
At this point the carrots and squash should be ready to come out. You want the squash to be totally cooked, but the carrots can still be a little firm.
Add the carrots to the pot, cover with a lid, and let simmer for 10-15 minutes.
While that's simmering, let your squash sit for 5-10 minutes to cool a bit, and then use a spoon to scoop out the flesh. Once scooped, you can add it to the pot.

Let everything continue to cook until the carrots are fork tender. They may be ready after the 10 minutes of simmering, but if not just give it another 5-10. Once ready, use an immersion blender to blend everything up! Pour in the coconut milk and blend again.

Pour into your favorite lil soup bowls, top with some extra coconut milk for garnish, some chili crisp, and the roasted nuts. Feel free to also top with some plain greek yogurt to sooth the heat, add protein, and creaminess! (you can also add some heavy cream here if you want the heat but don't want to be lit on fire... ya feel?)
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Spicy Squash n Carrot Soup
Description:
It’s loaded with nutrients, protein, fiber, and HEAT to refuel your insides. 👏🏻
Not to mention it’ll help boost your immunity and help you heal from all of the yucky viruses going around. 

And I’ll be honest. I’m a total baby when it comes to spice, so I top mine with extra greek yogurt to cut down on the heat, add creaminess, ANDDD add extra protein.
Notes: Step 9: If you do not have an immersion blender you and blend it in a traditional blender in batches!

ingredients.Name: 16oz noodles  macaroni, cavatappi , whatever you want!

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 425F.
Reserve 1/4 of the total cheese and set it aside.

Big a large pot of heavily salted water set over high high to a boil. Once boiling add in your noodles and cook to per package instructions - BUTTTT basically just to under al dente. So when you bite it in half you have a ring of uncooked pasta in the center.
Reserve 1 cup of pasta water, strain the pasta, and set it aside. (You can also boil and cook while you're making the sauce)
Set a large dutch oven over medium heat. Add in the butter and allow to melt.
Once the butter is melted add in the flour and whisk constantly to toast it. It'll go from a pale yellow to a graham cracker color - about 1-3 minutes.

Once toasted, add in milk the by the 1/2 cup. Pour in, whisk vigorously until combined, then add in more. It may be scary when you first add in the milk because it'll separate and sputter, but just mixie mix and it'll come together.
Once all the milk is added, lower the temp slightly and allow to cook for 3-5 minutes longer, stirring frequently. It'll continue to thicken up during this time.

Take 1/4-1/2 of the milk mixture and add it to a different bowl/vessel. Add the egg and mixie mix to combine. This is tempering the egg so that it doesn't cook and turn to scrambled eggs when you add it to the pot. Once mixed, add to the pot and whisk to combine.
Next add in the seasonings and dijon, mixie mix.

Then all of the cheese, minus that reserved 1/4, is gonna go in. You may want to add in 1/4 cup of water at this point just to help it all incorporate. But continue stirring and adding water by the 1/4 cup (IF NEEDED!!! YOU MAY NOT NEED EXTRA WATER) until all of the cheese is melted and the sauce is smooth.
Then add in the the cooked pasta and mixie mix to combine.
Prep a large casserole dish with some oil. This will help prevent sticking ANDDDD help it crisp up. I personally like to use a cast iron baking dish because it encourages crisping even more.

Add the Mac and cheese to the prepped dish, top with the remaining cheese, and bake at 425F for 10-15 minutes. At this point it should be bubbling and top crisping. If not, turn the broiler on and cook until the top is crispy and browning! This will go fast if you have to use the broiler so DO NOT WALK AWAY!! Literally check every like 30-60 seconds.
Allow to cool for 5-10 minutes before diving in and
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Gouda and Cheddar Baked Mac n Chzzz
Description:
This isn’t your typical mac n’ chz and that’s what makes it so perfect! 

It is the perfect combo of creamy and sharp thanks to the gouda and cheddar. It gets amped up with seasoned salt and smoked paprika (and cayenne if you’re feeling wild). Anddd we got some brightness from the dijon. Plus it’s perfectly custardy, cheesy, and crispy on top. 

Seriously this recipe is my GO TO every single Thanksgiving. 🦃
Well… it’s actually Daniel’s responsibly to make the Mac N’ Chz every year and he doesn’t it beautifully every time. 😘
Notes:
*How do you know if you need extra water? If the cheese is stubbornly not melting and the sauce is extremely thick, you need extra water!
*MAKE AHEAD! You can make this the day or 2 before and just stop once you get to the baking portion. Then bake it whenever you're ready! You can also make it up to 2 months in advance if you freeze it! Then just allow to thaw prior to baking.

ingredients.Name: medium sized sweet potatoes, skin removed and cooked

directions.Direction: Place the sweet potatoes in a bowl and mash up until no clumps remain. Word to the wise, if any chunks remain you WILL see it when you go to roll out the gnocchi.
Add the egg and mixie mix to combine.
Pour in 1 1/2 cups of all purpose flour and 1 tsp salt. Use your hands or a wooden spoon to mix until a dough begins to form.

Flour a clean work surface and dump out the sweet potato dough. Sprinkle with more flour and knead until a soft, but smooth and firm-ish dough forms. About 2 minutes. You will likely need to add flour to keep the dough from sticking to the counter and your hands, just try not to go past the 2 cups total amount.

Once you feel the dough is in a good place, pop it in a container or bowl and place in the fridge to firm up for about 20 minutes. (If you’re working in tandem with the chicken meatballs, start those while you’re waiting!)
Set a pot of heavily salted water over high heat to boil.

Once chilled, divide into 4 pieces. Working 1 portion at a time, roll out into a long strip/log until it is about 1 in thickness. Try your best to make the whole log the same thickness, but honestly it’s just homemade gnocchi it’s not that serious. Have fun with it.
Then use a ruler or your eyeballz and cut the log into 1 in pieces.
Use your hands or a bench scraper to toss the pieces in some flour to prevent sticking and add them to a bowl. Move on with the other 3 portions of dough.

Boil the gnocchi in 2-4 batches, all just depends on how big your pot is, and stir a little at the beginning to discourage sticking. Allow those to boil for 2-4, but once they rise to the top they’re done! Use a spider/strainer to remove and set aside while you boil the remaining batch(es).
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat and allow to brown slightly, about 4 minutes. You want it to smell toasty and sputter slightly.
Add in the sage, red pepper flakes, salt n’ pep and fry the sage for 1-2 minutes.
Add in the gnocchi and toss to coat.
If you’re making these with the chicken meatballs I like to add them in, cover the whole thing with parm, and toss to incorporate.
That’s it!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Sweet Potato Gnocchi n' Chicken Meatballz!
Description:
I'm putting this recipe together so you can have BOTH recipes in one spot. 
:)

ingredients.Name: finely chopped green onion, chives, or any soft fresh herb

directions.Direction: Preheat the oven to 350F and prepare a baking sheet by oiling the surface.
Add all of the ingredients to a large bowl and mixie mix to combine. You can always test cook a small portion before moving on to test for seasoning.
Use a 1.5 tbsp cookie scoop to portion out the meat mixture. It should yield 20 meatballs so you can also just divide and conquer!
Roll them out into neat lil ballz and space evenly on the cookie sheet.
Bake for 30-40 minutes, or until the internal temp reaches 165F and the bottoms are nice and crispy.
Allow to cool and
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Chicken Meat Ballz
Description:
I love meatballz. They're the easiest way for me to add protein to a meal.... well just ground meat is the easiest but this is the best easiest! 

They're lean with the chicken, but pack on tonz of flavor!

Great for meal prepping or just for dinner. Make these with the sweet potato gnocchi!

ingredients.Name: leeks, cut in half length wise then cut into 1/4 in half moons
of Yukon gold potatoes, chopped into 1.5 inch ish chunks
thick cut bacon, cooked and chopped

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 350F. Place bacon on a baking sheet in a single layer and bake for 20 minutes, flip, and then another 10-20 minutes more. Once nice and crispy just give that a chop! I stack all of the pieces, cut it length wise, then cut into about 1/2 in squares. While this is baking continue on with the rest of the recipe!
Heat a large dutch oven over medium heat and plop in the butter. Melt dat and then add in your leeks. Cook for about 5-7 minutes, or until nice and softened.
Add in garlic, give it a stir for about 20 seconds, then add in all of the bone broth (I used half chicken and half beef, so you do you!)

Use an immersion blender to blend that all up. While this isn’t totally necessary, it will yield a smoother and easier to eat soup at the end. Keep the blender handy because we’re going to use it again!

Add in potatoes and spinach and let that simmer for about 20 minutes, or until the potatoes are fork tender. At this point I personally like to give it another 3-4 pulses with the immersion blender just to add a littttttle more body with blended potatoes, but once again not totally necessary.

Add in the lemon zest, heavy cream and mixie mix to combine. Give the soup a lil taste and adjust the salt accordingly, I added about 1 tbsp. You want to err on the side of less salty because it will get additional salt from the cheddar cheese and bacon!
Generously fill up a soup bowl, top first with the cheese to make it meltyyyyy, bacon, then green onion.
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: THE Potato Leek Soup
Description:
Hellllllo soup seazon! Not kidding this recipe is EVERYTHING I want in a soup. 🤌🏻

It’s soooooo easy to make, it’s hearty, it’s filling, and it’s NUTRITIOUS! 
Like helloooo vitamins, minerals, antioxidants, and protein 👏🏻

I kept the ingredient list really intentional here so you don’t have to buy a gazillion things that you don’t actually need. 

Basically, it’s perfection. ✨
Notes:
*You can totally use fresh spinach, but I personally like the frozen stuff.
*If you add too much salt you can always add extra cream, water, or broth. 
*POSTPARTUM PREP: you can freeze in SouperCubes, deli containers, and you *MAY* be able to freeze in glass jars if you leave a significant amount of space at the top and don't tightly screw on a lid.

ingredients.Name: ground bison (Force of Nature with beef liver n stuff is super good)

directions.Direction: Make yo sauce. Brown onion and garlic in a couple tablespoons of tallow, ghee, or olive oil. Set that over medium heat and cook for about 5 minutes. Spoon it out of the pan n’ put it in a bowl.

Add another tbsp of oil and add in your ground beef in chunks, trying to not overlap anything. Season with salt and pep and cook over medium-high heat for about 5 minutes on the first side or until you get some serious browning. Flip it, break it up, remove it, and put it in a bowl. Repeat with the bison meat.

Add the anchovy filets to the pan and right when they start sizzling and popping everywhere add in your tomatoes. As you can tell from my red hand I like to smoosh them up in the can and then dump them in. Mixie mix then add in your meats, onions, and garlic. Mixie mix , salt and pep, and reduce the heat to low and allow to gently simmer while you prepare everything else - about 30 minutes.
Preheat your oven to 375F.

Boil your noods in heavily salted water per the package instructions for al dente. Strain out and separate so they don’t stick together as they cool. If they do, do your best to gently pull them apart - water or oil can help here but isn’t ideal. Worst case you just have a collage of noodles that’ll still taste great.
In a large bowl combine the ricotta, parm, egg, parsley and basil (holding back 1 tbsp herbs). Mixie mix.

To a 9x13 pan add about 1 cup of sauce and spread it evenly. Add a layer of noodz, 1/2 of the ricotta mix, using your hands to smooth it out, then 1/3 of your mozz. Repeat ending with noods and topping with the remaining 1/3 of mozz.
Bake for 40-50 min. Top with reserved herbs and extra parm. Let sit for about 15 min and then DIVE IN.

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Super MEATY Lasagna
Description: Ground Beef AND Ground Bison make this next level.

ingredients.Name: (Total of  cups of nuts and seeds, but this is what I did)
coconut oil, olive oil, or ghee melted

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 325F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.

Add the nuts and seeds to a food processor and pulse until the almonds and other large nuts are chopped, but not until you get a sandy mess. We want each nut to still be recognizable. *you can also do this by hand with a knife*
Add the coconut flakes, chopped nuts, chia seeds, cinnamon, and salt to a large bowl.
Combine the maple syrup, oil of choice, and vanilla extract in a small bowl.

Add that to the nut mix and mix to combine. You may need to add a bit more oil or syrup if the mixture seems too dry. This will all depend on how many nuts and seeds you actually used and how finely you processed them. We're looking for moistened, not soaked.
Pour onto the prepared cookie sheet and bake at 325F, undisturbed for 30-35 minutes. You are looking for fragrant and golden.
Immediately add in the dried fruit and mix to combine. Then allow to fully cool in the pan - clusters will likely form.
Store in an airtight container at room temperature and enjoy (for best taste) within a week.
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Lightly Sweetened Nut and Seed Granola
Description:
I think my life was forever changed when I tried Trader Joe’s all nut granola. *that’s an exaggeration… but you get what I’m saying” 

The thing is, while I do love some store bought granolas, they’re often WAY too sweet for my liking and packed with stuff I don't often eat (like oats). This one is lightly sweetened with some maple syrup. 

It’s perfect on yogurt, a smoothie bowl, cottage cheese, or even in a bowl with some milk and fruit. And did I mention just as a plain ol’ mid day snack???

This recipe is great because you can mix and match nuts and seeds to your liking. Just stick to the general ratios and you're good to go!
Notes: *I prepped this for postpartum! I just added it to Weck jars, leaving a bit of space at the top, and froze them. So once I want to use them I will thaw on the counter and re-toast if they need a little refresh.

directions.Direction: Combine everything in a VERY large bowl.
Scoop out into meatball sized portions - about 2 tbsp
Place on baking sheets (it took me 1 large and 2 small baking sheets)
Bake at 350F for 30 minutes - until the tops are browned and crispy
The underside will likely be a little soft after baking, so you can flip and broil until that side is browned as well
Let cool on a wire rack before transferring to freezer bags
Eat within 2-3 months

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Big Batch Meatball Postpartum Prep
Description: One of the easiest ways to add protein to any meal is through meatballs so I knew that I wanted to prep a ton of meatballs for the postpartum period. Obviously these will be delicious in pasta and red sauce, but I also add meatballs to rice and veggies, Mediterranean meals - think like, homemade cava, sub sandwiches, we can even jazz them up with a sweet and sour sauce or Swedish meatball sauce. They’re versitile and can be incorporated into almost any lunch or dinner. I’m so happy I have a bagjillion for the postpartum period.

ingredients.Name: rolled oats (I like One Degree Organic since they are organic and certified glyphosate free)
sourdough discard (you can replace with buttermilk)
melted butter, tallow, or coconut oil
nut butter (I like CB's Organics organic 100% peanut peanut butter)

directions.Direction: Combine oats, flour, brewers yeast, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in a large bowl. Set aside.
Combine sourdough discard, eggs, melted butter, vanilla, coconut sugar, and nut butter.
Add wet to the dry and mix to combine.
Use a cookie scoop to measure out about 24 cookies. Let chill for at least 30 minutes.
Use your palms to roll into a smooth ball.
**Either add to freezer bags and freeze until you’re ready to bake or move on to next step
Preheat oven to 350F and bake on a parchment lined baking sheet for 10-14 minutes. The top of the cookie will crack a bit and the edges will be golden.
Let cool on a wire rack.

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Peanut Butter Lactation Cookies
Description:
No, these will not make you spontaneously lactate if you didn’t just have a baby. HOWEVER the Brewers yeast does help boost milk production. 

Whether you're pregnant or not, these are DELICIOUS!

ingredients.Name: Ghee or other oil for frying eggs

directions.Direction: This honestly couldn’t be easier…
Fry eggs in ghee or other oil in batches. Season with salt and pepper.
Combine dijon and mayo in a small bowl. Add that to one side of each of the 12 English muffins.
Assemble English muffin with an egg, a sausage patty, a slice of cheese, and that’s it! Add to a freezer bag and reheat once you’re ready :)

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Sausage, Egg, and Cheese English Muffin
Description: These English muffins are perfect for the postpartum prep. The thing that really makes them shine? The chipotle dijonaise. 😮‍💨
Notes: I’ll likely reheat in my toaster oven at 250F for like 20 minutes… but I’m just guessing here.

ingredients.Name: to 3 dried chipotle chilis, hydrated and blended OR 2 tbsp chili powder
Toppings: cheddar cheese, cilantro, greek yogurt, more lime juice

directions.Direction: Cook the beef in a large dutch oven with some ghee, tallow, or oil, over medium-high until all sides are browned. Season with salt and pepper. Remove and set aside.
Add the onions, garlic, and peppers and sauté, scraping up the bottom browned bits, until softened.
Add in the mushrooms and cook until softened.
Add in the fire roasted tomatoes, blended chilis, and 2 cups of water. Once again scrape the bottom to get all those browned bits.
Add in the beef, beans, oregano, chili powder, cumin, and salt. Let simmer on low for at least 1 hour, but ideally 2.
Add the lime juice and maple syrup or honey.
Taste for seasoning, add extra water if it boiled down too much for your liking.
Top with cheddar cheese, yogurt, cilantro, and more lime juice.
ENJOY!
FREEZING: I added mine to 1 cup portioned Souper Cubes and then transferred to compostable ziplock bags once frozen. Eat within 4-6 months.

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Fairly Fancy Chili
Description:
This isn’t my traditional chili, this is my fairly fancy chili. 

I knew that I wanted to load up on as many nutrients as possible, so I included bell peppers, shiitake mushrooms, and thick chunks of beef stew meat.

ingredients.Name: jar of SAUZ Wild Rosemary Marinara
fresh parsley, finely chopped (or 1 tbsp dried)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 425F
Boil lasagna noodles in heavily salted water to just under al dente - they will continue to cook in the oven! Add in 1 tbsp of olive oil when you are cooking the noodles to help prevent any sticking.

Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat and add in a tbsp of olive oil or other oil. Cook the Italian sausage in chunks at first, leaving undisturbed for about 3-5 minutes, to achieve a nice browned crust on the bottom. Then use your spatula to break up the chunks and cook through. Use a slotted spoon to remove and set aside.

Add the ground beef to the pan and cook in the same method as the pork - adding in chunks and letting it brown before breaking it up. Season with salt and pepper. Use the slotted spoon to once again remove and set aside.

Add in the onions, lower the heat to medium, and sauté for about 5-7 minutes until softened and turning translucent. Add in the garlic and optional anchovy filets and cook for an additional 30 seconds.
Add the sausage and beef back in, mix to combine, then remove the pan from the heat.
Combine the ricotta, eggs, parsley, oregano, salt, and 1/2 of the parm. Set aside.
Combine the grated mozzarella and remaining 1/4 cup of parm.

Assembly time!! Get your baking dish and spread 1/3 of the sauce to the bottom of the pan followed by a layer of noodles, 1/2 of the ricotta mix (spread it out), 1/2 of the meat mix, and 1/4 of the mozzarella cheese. Repeat - 1/3 sauce, 1/2 ricotta, 1/2 meat, 1/4 cheese. Add the remaining sauce PLUS add some water to the jar, shake it up to get every little last bit of sauce, then pour that on top as well. Add the final layer of noodles and remaining 1/2 of the cheese.
Bake at 425F for 45 minutes or until the top is crisping and the sauce is bubbling around the sides. Let cool for AT LEAST 15 minutes.
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Wild Rosemary Marinara Lasagna
Description: When planning out postpartum freezer meals I KNEW that lasagna was a must have on that list. But no matter if you're pregnant, postpartum, or just someone that loves lasagna... this one will not disappoint.

ingredients.Name: box noodles (I prefer something tubular to capture sauce, but any shape will do!)
dry parsley (you can totally just use the fresh here if thats what you have)
jar pasta sauce (any flavor you like)
mozzarella, pulled apart into small chunks (please use fresh and not pre grated, but you do you)
finely chopped parsley, 1 tbsp reserved (and subsequently you can sub for dry if that’s all you have, but cut the amount dramatically. We’re talking like 1 tbsp inside the pasta and 1/2 tsp on top)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 350F
Cook noodles in heavily salted water until just under “al dente”. You want a thin ring of uncooked pasta in the center when you bite/cut it in half.

Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat and add a couple tablespoons of olive oil. Once the oil is shimmering, break up the beef into chunks and spread it out in the pan. You want the maximum surface area of the beef to be on the pan so it can properly brown. Because browning (Maillard reaction) means FLAVOR. ***don’t smoosh down the beef at this point. If you smoosh it then you’ll cover the entire surface of the pan and the beef will sort of steam. You want space between the pieces of beef if possible. ***

Season the first side with salt, pepper, dried basil, and dried parsley and cook for about 3-5 minutes. Test the doneness by flipping one piece, you’re looking for deeply browned and crispy but NOT burnt. If you burned it, well now you know for next time to lower the heat and cook for less time.

Flip all the pieces and use a spatula or spoon to break up all the chunks. You want tiny pieces of beef now. Add in the garlic at this point and gently stir/move around until no pink remains, then turn off the heat and set aside.
At this point your noodles should be cooked so drain those and add them back to the pot (cuz we’re not needlessly dirtying extra bowls).
Add in the beef, whole jar of sauce (you can start with half if that makes you happy and adjust to your saucy liking as you go), 3/4 of mozzarella, and the parsley MINUS the 1 tbsp reserved.
Mixie mix everything and then pour it back into the large skillet you used to cook the beef.
Gently smoosh is down so everything fits and top with the remaining 1/4 mozzarella and parm - quantity of parm is at your discretion, but you want a light coating over the whole top.
Place in the preheated oven and cook for 25 minutes or until the cheese is melted and sauce is slightly bubbling in the pan.
Top with remaining 1 tbsp parsley and dats it!
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: The EASIEST Baked Pasta
Description:
We’ve all been there. It’s the end of the day and jarred sauce, boxed noodles, and some cooked meat is all that’s happening for dinner. And no shade to that, it is absolutely comforting and filling. 👏🏻

BUT I wanted to create this recipe and video so you can see a couple lil tips and tricks to elevate that. It takes marginally more effort and yields huge results. 💥

Are there things we could do to make this better? Absotootly. But that’s not the point. Andddd it’s still super comforting, super filling, and will FEED YOU FOR DAYS. 😎

It has ooey gooey mozzarella on the inside and crispy parmesan on top. The beef gets browned for optimal maillard reaction flavor town 🤌🏻

PS - peep the noodle shot to see the exact level of “al dente” I cook my pasta to when it’s going to be baked. You want a thin line of uncooked pasta in the center. You’ll see what I mean. 😘

ingredients.Name: egg (2 will make them more tender)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 425F.
Combine everything in a medium bowl until just combined.

Use a 1.5 in cookie scoop (about 1 1/2 tablespoons) and portion it out. It should come out to 20 meatballs. Roll them out and evenly space on a quarter sheet pan. (Aka a smaller cookie sheet or literally whatever you have… use a cast-iron pan for all I care)
Cook until browning, crisping, and sizzling. About 28-34 minutes.
Dats it! Enjoy!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Grain Free PARMESAN Meatballs
Description:
Cuz sometimes you don't want grainz ya know? These are the perfect meal prep item in my book, but are perrrrfect in a spaghetti and meatball dish. 

The traditional breadcrumbs or bread is replaced with almond meal. They have parmesan for a little umami flavor, and parsley and garlic to even everything out.

ingredients.Name: 2 salmon filets, cut into  in cubes

directions.Direction: Preheat smoker to 200F OR oven to 400F.
Mixie mix maple syrup, soy sauce, and ginger in a bowl. Set aside.
Add salmon bits to a baking sheet (for whichever cooking method you’re using) and coat in the soy mixture. Evenly space the bites so they’re not touching. You want the heat to hit every bit of them!
If smoking, cook at 200F for 1 hour. If baking, cook at 400F for 15-20 minutes. You want them to be fully dry, browning, and a bit crispy.
That’s it! ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Soy Maple Ginger SALMON Bitez
Description:
I live laugh love meal prepping these babies because they are just about the perfect addition to everything. 🔥

They’re so easy to make, like literally FOUR INGREDIENTS, minimal prep, and then you can use them as you please. 

I made these in my little smoker, but you can absolutely do it in your oven instead.

HOW I USE THEM:
🍣As a standalone snack
🍣With rice and avocado for dinner
🍣In a homemade sushi roll 
🍣Alongside eggz for brekki

directions.Direction: Literally just mix everything in a large CLEAN bowl.
Add the salsa mix to a 1/2 gallon sterilized (can be done with HOT water and soap or in the dishwasher) and smoosh it down if needed. You want about 1-2 inches of space left on top.
Add a cabbage leaf to the top (in that remaining space) and close the lid.

Place the jar in a dark, cool area for 2-4 days. I HIGHLY advise checking on it after one day during the summer as it might ferment even faster. For reference mine was totally fermented and leaking after 2 days!
You can “burp” your jar after each day to help release some of the gasses. Basically that just means opening the lid and allowing excess gas to escape.
Once your salsa is bubbly, fizzy, and visibly different it is ready to go!
I love to eat it with chips, nachos, on burritos, eggs, basically anywhere you would normally eat salsa!
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: FERMENTED Tomato Salsa
Description:
One of my all time favorite summer recipes. It’s delicious and so so so good for you. 😎☀️

Fermenting at home can seem intimidating, but I promise you this recipe is the easiest way to get started! 

And why are fermented foods even important, you might ask?

WELL! Probiotics (found in fermented foods) may help:
🌸support gut health
☀️improve immune system
🦋improve anxiety, depression, and other mental health issues
🐝ease allergies
✨annnnnd is great for skin health. 
**These are seriously just to name a few.**

I originally found the recipe in the book “The Beauty Chef”, and have since adapted it to better fit my own needs/desires. 

I personally have trouble with peppers so I switched this up to have more garlic, ginger, and a little hot honey all for heat. 

PS PLEASE TRY TO GET EVERYTHING ORGANIC AND WASH EVERYTHING THOROUGHLY!

ingredients.Name: liquid rice seasoning (I used Dozens Cousins)_
veggies (I like onions, pepper, tomatoes, mushrooms, but you can use anything
10oz cans/containers of beans (I like black and

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 425F

Cook the rice according to the package instructions, BUT add in the ghee or butter and rice seasoning packet before the rice if you're using them. Set aside once cooked. *You can also use bone broth in place of the water for extra nutrients, protein, and flavor!

Cut all of your veggies and sauté them until softened. Season with salt n pep to taste. You don't want to take it too far because they'll continue to cook in the oven. Add the juice of one lime once it's done cooking. Set aside.

Assemble! Place a large baking dish inside a rimmed baking sheet, cuz spillage. Then add 1/2 of the veggies to the dish, then ALL of the rice, then meat, then cheese, then veggies, then the rest of the cheese!
Bake at 425F for 20-30 minutes or until the cheese is nice and melty and browning. Allow it to cool for 5-10 minutes, top with your optional toppings, and...
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Burrito Bowl Casserole
Description:
This recipe was originally created when we were in college and needed cheap, easy, and healthy food that could easily be reheated. It has remained a staple in my cooking routine because it's just that: easy, cheap, healthy and so so sooooo delicious. It is pure comfort food. 

PLUS! You can use literally any veggies you have on hand so it's a great waste free meal. 

This is of course perfect for dinner, but would also be great as a meal prep for lunches during the week too. You can also throw so fried eggz on top and call it breakfast!

*** Easy and worthwhile additions:
- Avocado
- Plain Greek Yogurt or Sour Cream
- Cilantro
- More Lime
- Hot Sauce

directions.Direction: Melt butter in a large pan over medium high heat. Add in grated garlic and cook until sizzling, but not browning. Literally only like 30-45 seconds!!
If you want to be crazyyyyy you can add a tbsp of olive oil here. Not necessary, but it'll add another layer of flavor.
Immediately add in heavy cream and mixie mix to combine. Add in parm, and you got it... mixie mix!

Let that simmer on medium-low for about 15-20 minutes or until it doubles in thickness. Aka it holds the streak when you run the spoon along the bottom of the pan OR when you run your finger down the spoon. Get it? You want to whisk/stir VERY frequently here so the parm doesn't burnt/scorch on the bottom.
If you take the sauce too far and it's too thick you can always add a splash of heavy cream, pasta water, or a little olive oil.
Season with salt n' pep to taste.
Dats it. ENJOY!!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: THE Alfredo Sauce
Description:
I could bathe in this. I could replace water with this. THIS is THE Alfredo Sauce. 

I'm definitely kidding... but it really is that delicious. And so stupid easy to make. Use this as a pizza sauce, pasta sauce, dip, or literally anything.

ingredients.Name: soft leaf herbs (basil, parsley, cilantro, dill, thyme leaves)

directions.Direction: Using either a bullet blender, small food processor, or mortar n' pestle, combine 1/4 cup olive oil, 1 cup herbs, 2 cloves garlic, and 1 tbsp pine nuts. You want this full blended/mixed together. I'm not going for a chunky pesto here.
If it's just like not mixing you can add extra olive oil, hence the 1/4-1/2 cup measurement.
Add in parm, salt n' pep, and mix once again to combine.
Dats it. ENJOY!!!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: HERBY Pesto!
Description:
I'm calling this herby pesto becauseeee you don't need to strictly stick to basil. While it's a total 10/10 with just basil, I've also made it with a mix of herbs and frankly it adds a lil something something. 

Only have basil? Perfect. Have basil, parsley, and some cilantro? Dope. Don't overthink it and just use what you have baby. 

But! This stuff is good on just about everything. Sandwiches, pizza, eggs, meat, fish, pasta salad, if you can think it you can pesto it.

ingredients.Name: dough (I use the Whole Foods dough cuz it’s SO good… trust me)
mozzarella… and hear me out, use pre shredded…
basil leaves (can also do 1/2 basil 1/2 parsley, or any herby combo that you have on hand!)

directions.Direction: Preheat Ninja Oven to Bake at 375F and fill with pellets for smoking. You can also bake in a conventional oven.
Chop chicken breast into 1.5 in pieces, drizzle 1ish tbsp olive oil, season with salt, pepper, and 1 tsp dried oregano. Cook on a baking/roasting sheet at 375F for 15 minutes.

Once the chicken is cooked, remove it and set aside. Place your pizza stone in the oven and set it AS HIGH AS IT GOES. For the Ninja that’s 700F, for my conventional oven that’s 500F. We want that stone rippin hot when the pizza goes in so the crust gets all nice n' crispyyy.

While the chicken is cooking, make the pesto! Add basil, 1/4 cup olive oil, 2 cloves garlic, 1 tbsp pine nuts, and some salt n pep to a small food processor or bullet blender. Blend until combined and smooth. If it’s just like not blending and you're getting frustrated, don't fret! You can add extra olive oil (hence the 1/4-1/2 measurement). Then add in 1/2 cup grated parmesan and blend again until combined and smooth. Add to a squeeze bottle if you wanna be fun, but totally not necessary. Set aside.

Next up is the ALFREDOOO! Seriously the best sauce ever. Ok melt 4 tbsp butter in a large pan over medium heat. *if you're feeling wild and free add in 1 tbsp olive oil* OOOOH OFF SCRIPT! Add in the 2 cloves of grated garlic and stir until they’re sizzling, but not browning… literally only like 30-45 seconds. Add in the heavy cream and remaining 1 cup parm, whisk to combine, and gently simmer, mixing frequently, until it is thick enough that it holds a streak on the back of the spoon. About 15 minutes. Season with salt n pep and set aside. *If ya take it too far wit the simmer and need to thin it out you can add a splash of cream orrrr some olive oil. You choose your adventure. Both are delish.

Prepare your dough ball, top with a layer of the Alfredo sauce leaving a boarder for the crust (you may not use all of the sauce, but hey that’s perfect for dipping ya know), add enough cheese to cover the Alfredo but you can still see tiny spots of it poking through, then chicken, then a tad more cheese and some freshly grated parm. Bake for about 3 minutes at 700F or 10 minutes at 500F. Take it out, either drizzle or dollop with the pesto, then pop it back in for about 2-4 minutes respectively until the pesto is a lil melty and the crust is blistered and brown. *If the pesto leaches too much oil you can dab it with a paper towel to absorb the excess, then bake for one additional minute.
Cut it up, dip in some marinara, and ENJOY!!!!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Chicken Alfredo Basil Pesto PIZZA
Description:
This truly might be one of the most delicious thingz I have EVER made. Full stop. No exaggeration... And listen, anyone that has tried it (which shockingly is a lot of people because I threw a big ol pizza party) agree with me 100%. 
Each component of this is a masterpiece on its own and deserves to be celebrated. But together... FIREWORKZ. 
Make this make this make this!!!!

ingredients.Name: Heavily season with salt and pep

directions.Direction: In a large sauce pan, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add in onion and garlic and cook until softened, about 3-5 minutes. Add in anchovies, mixie mix. Then add tomatoes and basil. Let that gently simmer over medium-low for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally (while you cook the meatballs).
Then use an immersion blender to blend that up. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
For da meatballs you literally just mix all of the ingredients (linked) in a large bowl. Divide into even balls that are about 2 tbsp each.
Bake at 425F for 12ish minutes, or until the bottoms are browning and internal temp is 160F. Add to your sauce, and mixie mix that up.
Slice the baguette in half, remove some bread from the bottom half to hallow it out, and drizzle with olive oil.

Broil cut side up for a couple minutes to toast. Then remove from the oven and fill up the bottoms with meatballs, top with extra sauce, a layer of mozzarella, and then pop it back in the oven on broil to melt/bubble the cheese. Remove from the oven, top with some extra parsley, your baguette top, and slice that baby in half, quarters, whatever feels good to you.
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: MEATBALL SUBZ
Description:
These are stupid delicious and honestly so easy peasy to make. 
It’s filling enough to feed a crowd… or just a really really super hungry you.

ingredients.Name: Mac and cheese, precooked and refrigerated

directions.Direction: Set a large pot over medium heat with oil for frying… while you don’t neeeeeed to fully submerge them, it will give you the most even coloring and fry. So work with what you have is what I’m saying.

Scoop out 1/2 cup sized portions of your Mac and cheese. This yielded 9 balls for me. Roll them into uniform portions and smoosh to flatten out. *Refrigerated Mac and cheese is best so it holds together. The warmer it gets the harder it will be to work with.

Add about 1 tbsp worth of mozzarella (each brand will vary in size so just use your judgement here) and then roll that puppy up. Make sure no mozzarella is poking out, we don’t need any frier explosions.
In 3 bowls, add flour to one, egg and water to another, and panko to the third. Season each with salt and pepper and give them a lil mixie mix.

Now to dredge! Working one ball at a time and keeping one hand wet and one dry, begin the dunks. First coat in flour, shake off excess. Then use the other hand to coat in egg, shake off excess. Then coat in panko! I like to gently press the panko in to ensure maximum adhesion. Repeat with remaining balls.

Once the oil is hot (you don’t want it smoking but you doooo want a lil sizzle when you plop in a small test panko piece). Most people don’t have instant read thermometers so that’s the benchmark I’m giving you. (If you do tho you can heat to 350F ;) )
Gentttttly add the ballz to the pot and fry for about 3-5 minutes, rotating as needed, until the ball is deeply golden and crispy.
Use a spider (or tongs, or whatever you have) to strain on a wire rack. Immediately season with some extra salt.
Allow to cool, unless you want to burn your entire mouth then go right ahead.
Dunk those babies in some heated marinara annnnnnd
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: FRIED Mac n Cheeeeze Ballz 🧀
Description:
This one is for all of you that thought the Mac and Cheese was unhealthy. 😘

Deez mac n chz ballz are filled with teeny tiny leetle Mozzarellas, rolled up, breaded, and FRIEEED! Cuz health. 

Jk these are NOT healthy but like really yummy dipped in marinara. 😎

ingredients.Name: green onions, cut on a bias

directions.Direction: Alrighty let’s mix up da sauce! Add fish sauce, brown sugar, lime juice, soy sauce, sambal, garlic, and ginger to a mason jar or bowl and mixie mix dat up. Set aside.
Cook noods according to package directions, but make sure you cook until just under al dente per usual. It’ll finish cooking in the sauce!

I like to season the chicken with fish sauce and pepper to help round out the sauce sitch. That’ll cook first so we can get some yummy chicken flavor in the pan. Speaking of pan, coat the bottom of the pan with oil and cook chicken over medium high heat. Really let it go on the first side to get some serious enzymatic browning - about 5 minutes. Then just toss and mix around to finish fully cooking. Remove from pan and move on.

Next up, VEG! Add some more oil if you need, then plop in the red bell pepper, broccoli, and green onions. Once again let that go for about 5 minutes on the first side so you get a lil char on one side. Idk that’s just how I like it, but you do you. Then mixie mix around and cook another 2ish minutes to further soften.
Push veggies over to the side, add oil to the empty side of the pan, and add in the eggz. Scramble those bad boys up! Once fully cooked just combine it with the veg.

Lower heat and add carrots, mung beans, noodles, and sauce. Mix that all up and cook until the sauce thickens and noodles absorb the liquid, about 3 minutes. Add cooked chicken, smashed peanuts, and mix to combine.

ASSEMBLY! Get a hefty portion and top it with some more smashed peanuts, cilantro, mung bean sprouts, maybe some outrageously hot red chili slices, lime wedges, idk whatever makes you feel happy ya know.
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Veg Heavy Chicken PAD THAI
Description:
I love a Pad Thai that goes heavy on the veggies, protein, and toppings. 🤌🏻
So easy peasy to make without sacrificing any flavor.

ingredients.Name: American cheese, either unwrapped or cut into cubes

directions.Direction: First things first, cook yo noods. I personally like to go with something unique here (not shells or macaroni), but honestly anything you put in it would be delish. Like cheesy spaghetti? Sure sign me up. Whatever you use, make sure you only cook until al dente. Strain and set aside once ready.
In a large pan or pot, melt butter over medium heat. It’ll melt faster if you cut it up, but that’s totally not necessary.
Add in the evaporated milk and mustard and mixie mix. Best to use a whisk, but use whatever you have!

Time to temper the eggs! Crack two eggs into a heatproof bowl or cup, beat until no large streaks remain, add in a couple tablespoons of the milky mixture, and mixie mix! This will slowly bring up the temperature of the eggs so that when you add it to the pan it doesn’t immediately scramble.
Slowly stream in the egg mix into the pan while stirring/whisking.

Now to “temper” the corn starch. Add cornstarch to a small bowl and add a little bit of that milky mixture. Mixie mix until it smooths out and no clumps remain. Thennnn you can lower the heat to low and add it into the pan! This will greatly thicken the sauce.
Add in cheeses and stir until fully melted, a couple minutes.

And listen, the sauce is gonna be THICK. So you’re probably gonna have to add in 1 cup of water. You have some options. You can just test your luck and add in the pasta and see if it’ll combine to your desired consistency and if it doesn’t you gradually add in water… orrrr you just commit to needing water and add it in prior to the pasta. I know that’s annoying. Sorry. The perk to adding post pasta is that you can see exactly how much you actually need without over diluting the sauce. Either way, stir until fully combined and coated.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and dats it!!
Enjoy!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Ooey Gooey Mac and Cheese
Description:
It’s comfort in a bowl, idk what else to tell ya. It’s the mac and cheese you remember eating as a kiddo, but like actually delicious. 
The sharp cheddar cheese and mustard make this insanely flavorful, while the American “cheese” gives it that ooey gooey texture and shine that you remember.

ingredients.Name: small eggplant, I used the graffiti variety
tropea onion, sub with 1 large shallot
pasta, I used the Trofie Pasta from Trader Joe’s but any small fun shape’ll do

directions.Direction: Prep yo veggies. Cut off the stem of the eggplant and slice in half lengthwise, peel and thinly slice onion, peel and thinly slice garlic, and roughly chop your tomatoes. Season the eggplant with a little salt and pepper.

Let’s cook the pasta! Bring a big ol pot of heavily salted water to boil and throw in your pasta. Cook according to the package directions, but keep in mind we want to cook it until just under al dente so it can finish cooking in the sauce.

But here’s the tricky part, we want to time the pasta with the sauce being done, so I recommend having the boiling water ready and then adding the pasta in once your onions and garlic are browned. If it isn’t timed perfectly don’t fret, just strain the pasta and save about 1 cup of pasta water for the sauce.

Grab a big ass pan and add enough olive oil to coat the bottom. Set that puppy up to medium high heat and pan fry the eggplant until browned and crispy, about 3-5 minutes. Remove from the pan and set aside.
There should still be a good amount of olive oil in the pan. Add in the sliced onion and garlic and cook, stirring frequently, until they are starting to soften, about 3-5 minutes.
Lower the heat to medium and add in the tomatoes. Cook until everything is softening and turning into a bit of a sauce. Don’t forget to season with a litttttle bit of salt and pep!

Use a spider or strainer to transfer the pasta into the sauce. Add in 1/2-1 cup pasta, depending on how much you need to bring everything together. Mixie mix until the pasta and sauce are fully combined. Let that cook down on medium low for about 3 minutes.

While the sauce is cooking down, separate basil leaves into two piles, one small leaves and one big leaves. Chiffonade the large leaves by stacking them all, rolling, and then thinly slicing. The small leaves are going to be used as garnish.

Remove the pan from heat and add in the chiffonade basil, mixie mix. Then add in about 6 anchovy filets. BUT here’s the deal with the chovies. If you’re chovie adverse I highly recommend adding them in while you’re cooking the onions and garlic so you get the flavor without the large pieces. If you loveeee anchovies add them in off the heat and while they will break up a bit when you mix everything, you’ll still have some larger, super salty, ultra umami bitz.

PLATING! A hefty serving of the pasta, a bunch o’ freshly grated parm, about 3-4 eggplant slices, some tiny basil leaves, extra olive oil, and extra pepper. I ended up wanting even MOREEE parm, so just keep that chunk readily available.
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: A Bright Eggplant n’ Tomato Pasta
Description:
Literally what’s better than cooking with super fresh, locally grown produce? Idk probably nothing. 
I wanted to highlight these gorgeous ingredients in a simple way so BOOM, a lil bright eggplant n’ tomato pasta 🍅

The onion, scallion looking thing is a Tropea Onion and y’all it was phenom. Andddd the eggplants are a graffiti variety so super small, a little sweeter, and just straight up cute. 

Oh and yeah, there’s anchovies in it cause YUM. Don’t hate. 😘

ingredients.Name: pork butt (shoulder, Boston butt, etc etc)

directions.Direction: Season yo meat. Start with salt and pep and then mixie mix your garlic powder and chili and slather that on.
Mix up the sauce (bbq sauce, acv, honey, dijon, Worcestershire, and giardiniera)
Drizz the olive oil in the croc pot and place the meat down first.
Add in the chopped onions and top with the saucy sauce. Cover and COOK!
I did high for 6 hours, but whatever time frame works for you will be fine.
Once done just give it a lil shred, toasty toast some bunz, and top with the giardiniera.
ENJOY!!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Pulled Pork Sammi w/ Giardiniera
Description: These pulled pork sammis with @carusoprovisions GIARDINIERA are beyonddddd. And so stupid easy to make.

ingredients.Name: finely chopped crab meat. If you want to use real crab legs you’ll need 1/2 lb. To cook: boil for about 3 minutes.
plain cream cheese, room temp ideally
white granulated sugar (yes, you need it)
Hot Crispy Oil, PLUS more for dipping doiiii

directions.Direction: Combine cream cheese, chives, salt, sugar, and hot crispy oil. Mixie mix until fully combined, then add in the crab meat.
Mixie mix again.

It’s smartest to only fill a couple won ton wrappers at a time because they dry out. If you want to be like me and put them all out and fill at one time just have a spray bottle of water to spritz them as you go.

Add 1/2 tbsp to the center of the wrapper, dip a finger in your water, and wet the outer edge of the wrapper. Grab two opposing corners and bring them together to make a triangle, pinch together to seal. Then fold each of the other corners into the center, then smoosh all of the corners together.
Basically like a little square pyramid of crab rangoon goodness.
It takes practice so just do your best and pay attention to sealing all edges!!!
*it’s smart to do this with a splatter pan on top of the oil in case you have any explosions. If you do have an explosion use a small wire mesh strainer to scoop out the filling.*
Heat the oil to 375F (or medium-high) and cook about 2 minutes or until the little rangoon baby is fully browned and crispyyy.
Drain on a wire rack and sprinkle with kosher salt.
Dip in more Hot Crispy Oil OR spoon it over.
Drooling….

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Crab Rangoon w/ HOT CRISPY OIL
Description: These suckers are so good. They have the original Hot Crispy Oil inside the filling and are perfection dipped in it post frying.

ingredients.Name: red pepper, seeds and core removed, sliced
orange pepper, seeds and core removed, sliced
12oz of salsa, I used Trader Joe’s Pineapple Salsa
~2 hot sauce, i used Smokey Chipotle Sauce
A couple large tortillas (cause it’s none of my business how many quesadillas you make, but about  4)
Some cilannnntroooo, basically to taste baby
Lime juice for sprinklin on top

directions.Direction: For The Chicken
Put all dat in a croc pot, cook for your desired time, and fagettaboutit. Seriously, it’ll work in 4 hours and it’ll work in 8. You do you boo.
Once it’s done just shred it up and you’re ready to use it! Make sure you “drain” off liquid before adding it to your dilla so you don’t have a soupy mess.
For The Dilla

Heat a large cast iron pan over medium / medium-high heat. Add your tortilla, then sprinkle on about 1/4 of the cheese, add some chicken mixie to 1/2 of the tortilla, some cilantro, a leeeetle more cheese, then fold that baby in half. Cook until BOTH sides are crispy n golden. Seriously the chicken has moisture so you want to make sure your tortilla is crispy.
Cut it in thirds, sprinkle with that lime juice, and if you’re feeling crazy add extra hot sauce and maybe some plain greek yog on the side.
It’s lunchtime as I write this and I’m about to go make another.

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Best Chicken QUESADILLA
Description:
I basically inhaled this. A must make. A MUST. 

This recipe SCREAMS meal prep and weeknight.
The hardest part is chopping the peppers and onions, dats it.

ingredients.Name: 4 Green Plantains, peeled and cut into  pieces
avocados, skin and pit removed. DOI.
medium yellow or white onion, finely diced. About 1/4
smoked paprika. Regular is fine… but just fine.

directions.Direction: For The Tostones
Heat oil in a large cast iron skillet over medium-high heat and cook all your lil plantain bits for about 3 minutes each side, until they are starting to get some browning color, then remove.

Smoosh each piece and cook for another 2ish minutes on each side, or until nice and crispy and golden. Best practice is to drain them on a wire rack, but you do you. Sprinkle with salt immediately after removing from the pan and boom. Dat easy.
For The Guacamole
Smoosh all of your avocados in a large bowl, leaving behind some chunky bitz. Add in all other ingredients, mixie mix. And dats it. Taste and see what else your little heart desires.

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: FRIED Plantains and GUACAMOLE
Description:
Tostones, aka, fried green plantains. AKA, one of my absolute, all time, peak favorite snackz. 

These lil babiez are double fried in TALLOW (cause we all know I be frying in tallow) and then DUNKED in some guac. What could be better?

ingredients.Name: ghee (I used the 4th & Heart pink sea salt ghee)

directions.Direction: Add your grated zucchini and carrots to a kitchen towel and wring them out to get as much liquid out as possible. The more liquid you get out the better they’ll hold up and crisp up.
Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and mixie mix to combine. Dump in the zucchini, carrots, chz, and egg. Mixie mix with your hands until it holds together when mushed.
Heat up the ghee (or other oil) in a large pan over medium-high heat. Cook for about 3-4 minutes on each side or until nice n crispy n deeply golden brown.
Spritz with some lemon juice and let them cool for a mini so you don’t burn your entire mouth. Dunk those suckers in some yog and enjoy!!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: CHEEESY Carrot Zucchini Fritterz
Description:
These suckers are so freaking good. I like to dip em in plain ol’ greek yog for some extra tangy protein, but you do you.
They have an egg, cheese, and almond meal for extra protein and holding power.

ingredients.Name: large of pepperoni, cut into 1/8 in squares
red sauce, frozen into cubes (YES, FROZEN!!)

directions.Direction: I used Bobby Flay’s pizza dough recipe here and just cut it in half.
Place your muffin tin in the oven and preheat it to 450F. We’re intentionally heating the muffin tin first to help the edges and bottom of the muffins crisp up.
Divide your dough into 6 pieces. If you can use a scale that would be preferred. Roll into balls then roll out into 6-8in rounds, thinning it out around the edges.
If you want to be crazy you can divide your mozzarella and pepperoni cubes in 6 so you have the exact amount in each muffin. Add 2-3 cubes of sauce - my cubes were approx 1/2in x 1in.
The frozen cubes are important because we need to assemble the muffins PRIOR to putting them in the muffin tin and if it’s liquid sauce it’s just messy and doesn’t hold together, ok? Ok.
Fold up the muffins after filling them, sealing the bottoms and laying them flat on their butts/seams to rest.

Your oven should be preheated by now so remove your muffin tin and put it on a rimmed baking sheet. Use a pastry brush to coat the tins with some melted butter. Carefully add a muffin to each lil hole, brush over more butter, and bake for 15-20 minutes or until deeply golden. Wait 5-10 minutes until diving in because these suckers are basically lava.
Some of your muffins will probably explode out the sides and leak saucey cheesy goodness so just don’t sweat it. They’re delish regardless.
Dip in extra red sauce and ENJOY.

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: PIZZA MUFFINS
Description: Is it pizza? Is it a muffin? It’s a PIZZA MUFFIN!

ingredients.Name: medium sized cauliflower, cut half, cored, and thinly sliced (it’ll fall apart)
medium sized yellow onion, thinly sliced
Several sprigs of chives, thinly sliced into baby chive tubes

directions.Direction: Preheat your oven to 425F.
Using a small saucepan over medium heat, combine your butter, heavy cream, dijon, and garlic.

Once combined turn off the heat, take a couple tablespoons and add it to a heatproof bowl/cup and then crack in your egg. Give that a whisk to temper the egg, adding another tablespoon or two to bring up the temp even more. Then slowly, while whisking, stream it into your saucepan. Season with salt n pep.
To assemble, use a heatproof dish approximately 8x8 or 9 inches large.

First add 1/2 cauliflower, 1/2 onion, 1/2 cheese, and repeat. Top it all off with your sauce and some more salt and pep. Place the dish on a baking sheet and a lid (or cookie sheet, aluminum foil, etc etc) on top. Bake for 20 minutes with the lid on, then remove and cook for another 25-30 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.
While the cauliflower is cooking, cook your bacon. I like to just bake it in the oven on a wire rack, but you do you. Once cooked cut it up into lil bacon crumblez.
Once the cauliflower is baked give it 10-20 minutes to cool down and firm up a bit. Top with bacon, chives, and dive innnnnn!
Enjoy!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Cheesy Cauliflower Bake w/ BACON n Chives
Description: For when you’re craving mac n chz, but want to be healthy n stuff. This cauliflower bake gets EXTRA protein from an egg in the sauceee and bacon on top.

ingredients.Name: chicken breast, butterflied and pounded to 1/2in thick (sliced half so you have 2 chicken pieces)
fire roasted red pep, cut half

directions.Direction: For The Goat Cheese Spread
Mixie mix it all together. Done.
For The Sammi
Season both sides of your chicken breast with salt and pepper.

Set your pan over medium high heat, slather with butter, and cook your chicken for about 3-4 minutes on the first side (until deeply golden) and about 2 minutes on the second side. It’ll all depend on how thin/thick your chicken is so use your judgement and a thermometer if needed. Remove and set aside.
Add more butter and toast BOTH sides of your bread.
Take two slices of your toasted bread and spread about half of the goat cheese mix on each (those will be the base of your sammis).
Top with your chicken, red pepper half, cabbage, carrot, cucumber, romaine, and then drizzle with some red wine vin. Top it all off with the other slice of bread, cut in half, and ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Chicken Veggie Sammi w/ Herby Goat Chz
Description:
Y’all, this chicken veggie sammi is out of this world. 

Don’t fret, I will be sharing the sourdough recipe soon, it just seemed like a lot for one video… Ya know?

ingredients.Name: limes, one for juicing one cut for garnish
mango, diced (pro tip: use a cup to separate the flesh from the skin)

directions.Direction: For The Slaw
Combine your cabbage, garlic, juice of 1 lime, and olive oil. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Set aside.
For The Taco Sauce
Combine yogurt, mayo, hot sauce, and smoked paprika. Set aside.
For The Fish
Season your fish with salt, pepper, cumin, paprika, and chili powder. No need to really measure, just evenly sprinkle it all over both sides.

Heat up a pan with tallow* over medium high heat. Depending on the thickness of your cod you may have to adjust, but about 3-5 minutes on both sides should do the trick. You’re looking for golden and crisping ok? Ok.
If you have a gas stove heat up your tortillas directly on the flame (BE CAREFUL AND DON’T START ANY FIRES!), if not you can wrap them in a damp paper towel and microwave them.
Assemble to your liking, add extra salt if needed, and enjoy.

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Fish Tacos w/ Slaw n’ Mangos

directions.Direction: Combine water, parm, butter, heavy cream, garlic, and 2 tbsp olive oil in the baking pan (the baking piece with high walls). Season with some salt and black pepper.
Add in pasta and give it a lil mixie mix.
Add the WHOLE bag of spinach and all of the sun-dried tomatoes (minus the oil). Carefully mix that because trust me, it’s a lot! But don't stress it'll all come together beautifully.
Gently smoosh it down and place it in the bottom portion of the combi.

Place all chicken breast on the baking tray and drizzle another 1 ish tbsp olive oil over the top. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder. Then flip and repeat the process of oil and spices. I personally like to flip once more so I know the spices have been fully coated in olive oil all over.

Place that in the top portion of the combi. Set it to Combi Meals and cook at 375F for 15 minutes for perfectly juicy and crispy chicken OR 390F for 15 minutes for well done but still juicy and crispy chicken. The pasta will somehow cook perfectly here too!
Once cooked remove and let the chicken rest before cutting. Mix the pasta to give the sauce a chance to fullllllly combine and get creamy.
Plate in a bowl or on a plate with a healthy serving of pasta and sliced chicken on top.
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Chicken Alfredo PASTA wit Sun dried Tomatoes n’ Spinach
Description:
This recipe was made with the Ninja Combi and it’s basically magic. Meal prep friendly and from start to finish it only takes 20 minutes - 15 of that is hands off cooking. I truly wish every busy person could have one of these. And if you’re lucky enough to own one, here is your recipe! 
PS - it’s basically a double batch of my Alfredo sauce, but you don’t even need to make the sauce you just add all the ingredients and POOF. Magic.

ingredients.Name: One batch of THICK Focaccia (recipe below!)
One batch of Easy Tomato Sauce (recipe below!)
mozzarella, sliced into 1/2in thick rounds whole milk low moisture

directions.Direction: Ok let’s talk focaccia! That’s the base of this pizza (obvs) but we aren’t cooking it all the way through like normal.

So step one: prepare and bake focaccia IN THE 9X13X3in PAN as normal at 425F, but for only 25 minutes. This will give it time to puff up and brown slightly before we cover it in sauce and cheese. Remove it from the oven.

So that brings us to step two: cover in sauce leaving a little border around the edges. You likely won’t use all of the sauce here (you may have about 1/2-1 cup leftover), but that’s great!!! Because then you can use it as a dip and if there’s one thing I personally love with my pizza, it’s a dip.

Cover the sauce with mozz slices and once again you probably won’t use the full 16 oz. I mean I’d be shocked if you did but listen who am I to judge? I personally like 6 slices cuz then it feels like personal little squares of pizza when cut. It’s cute.
Bake for another 20 minutes, rotating half way to make sure it browns evenly.
Remove from the oven, drizzle with extra olive oil, and sprinkle with flaky salt.
Allow to cool for about 10 minutes in the pan. Thennnn remove it from the pan and top with some basil leaves.
Cut into 6 slices (or however many slices you want) anddddd
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Focaccia PIZZA
Description:
It’s sauceyyy. It’s cheesyyyy. It’s THICCCC. 

It’s the perfect mix between a light and fluffy focaccia and a thick, chewy, crispy crust. 🔥
The sauce is subtly sweet and comes together so easily. It all gets topped with some mozz (duh) for that cheesy goodness we’re all looking for. And can’t forget the fresh basil to top it all off 🤌🏻

Is it tradish? No. Is it delish? YES. 😎

directions.Direction: Heat oil in a large pan over medium heat. Once shimmery add in onions and garlic.
Let those cook, tossing around frequently, until they are translucent and SOME of the edges of the onions are starting to brown.

Here’s the deal with the tomatoes. I like to add in the juice from the can first then stick my hand in the can and smoosh the tomatoes up that way. Thennn I pour the whole thing in. You could also just like, just your wooden spoon or a potato masher while they’re in the pan but that can get messy and is way less fun.

Throw in the basil leaves and reduce the heat to medium-low (or even closer to low) and allow to gently simmer for 20-30 minutes or until the sauce has dramatically reduced but there is still some liquid in there.

Pull out the sprigs of basil (or leave them in there if you love basil like dat) and you can either just leave it like this for a lil chunkier sauce orrrrrr use an immersion blender to blend it all up. *just don’t blend for super long or else you’ll turn the sauce orange*
Season with salt and pepper to taste annnnd
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: Easy Tomato Sauce
Description: It’s just simple. It’s what an easy, homemade tomato sauce should it. It’s dependable. It’ll get the job done. It’s always there for you. And yes, it’s super tasty.

ingredients.Name: beef chuck roast, bone in if possible
oil (olive, ghee, tallow, camel, coconut, anything works!)
celery stalks, cut into 1/2 in pieces
small medium butternut squash, peeled, seeded, and cut into 1 2in chunks
small yellow onion, sliced into half moons
medium sized carrots, chopped into 1 in pieces
Salt n’ pep for seasoning meat

directions.Direction: While browning the meat isn’t necessary, it will help impart some delicious flavor so I highly recommend. Heat up a large skillet with about 1 tbsp oil over medium-high heat. Once hot add in your chuck roast!
Season the exposed side with salt and pepper, and allow to cook for 3-5 minutes, or until you start developing a brown crust on the bottom.
Flip and cook another 3-5 minutes, seasoning that side as well.

Once you see that crust forming on the 2nd side, pour in the 1 cup of wine and allow to boil up and reduce slightly. Just like 1-2 minutes. This will also allow you to scrape up and browned bits on the bottom of the pan.
*If you don't have time or feel like browning the meat just skip all dat and season the meat, then add it and the wine to the crockpot.
Add the beef and wine to the bottom of the crock pot. Add in literally the rest of the ingredients, set it to your desired time, and let it cook!!
Once done, remove the meat and add it to another bowl. Shred it into bite sized pieces and then add back to the crockpot.
Eat as is or top with some plain greek yogurt.
ENJOY!

Creator: thetessasmith
Name: CrockPot Beef Stew
Description:
It's loaded with hearty veggies and squash to boost the nutrients anddddd cozy factor. 

And the best part? You just set it n’ forget it and then have food for DAYZZZZ. We love a crockpot. 👼🏻

In the video I only cooked it for 4 hours, but the longer you go the more tender the meat will become. But trust me, it's still PHENOM even after 4 hours.

ingredients.Name: olive oil, plus more for topping
freshly grated parm, plus more for topping
Extra salt and fresh cracked black pep for seasoning

directions.Direction: Set a large pot of heavily salted water over high heat to boil. Cook pasta until just under al dente (you’ll want to throw it in around the same time you are done simmering off the alcohol… don’t worry I’ll remind you)
Add olive oil to a dutch oven or large pot set over medium high heat.
